gomodel:SYNGO_767  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: The paper quantitatively describes the distribution of GAT-1 and GAT-3 at the rat cortex using pre-embedding peroxidase labeling and postimbedding immunogold labeling.\nFigure 2: electron microscopy images of peroxidase-based immunoreactivity in preembedded material of cortical layers 2-3. In figure 2e dendritic labeling is evident. Figure 2I quantifies the fraction of profiles where immunoreactivity was observed in axons or dendrites.\nFigure 4a-g expands this analysis . In 4D,E example images of immunoreactivity in axon terminals, perisynaptic astrocytic processes and post-synaptic elements are shown. In figure 4g a quantification of fraction of profiles where immunoreactivity was observed in the above-mentioned cellular compartments, with a further division into symmetric and asymmetric synapses.\n\nTaken together, the data supports a postsynaptic localization of GAT-1.. Experimental description: 'A quantitative analysis of cellular and synaptic localization of GAT-1 and GAT-3 in rat neocortex'. 'Animals and tissue preparation Adult male albino rats (200-225 g; n = 7; Sprague-Dawley, Charles River, Milan, Italy) were used.'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_767" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

